<div id="modal-lunch" class="modal hide fade">
  <div class="modal-header">
    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
    <h3>For Lunch</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="modal-body">
		<p><strong>Le Gaïac:</strong> A casual lunch menu and great sea views invite you to our restaurant for lunch time, definitely a different experience from the evening. On Sundays we welcome you to our famous Brunch, always a great “get together”. From 11:00 am onwards. Open every day. Restaurant closed from July 30th to October 25th included. Breakfast, lunch and dinner available in the room or on your private terrace</p>
		<p><strong>La Case de L’Isle (at Hotel Isle De France):</strong> Located on Flamands beach it serves French Mediterranean cuisine with entrees from the grill. Choose between eating on the deck or with your feet in the sand. Always busy so make sure you ask our reception to reserve in advance. Sun beds can be rented upon availability. Open every day.</p>
		<p><strong>Sand Bar at Eden Rock Hotel with Jean Georges:</strong> a must – Enjoy a day on the beach and lunch at the Sand Bar. Sun beds can be rented upon availability. Open every day.</p>
		<p><strong>Le Taiwana:</strong> Next to Isle de France on Flamands beach you can enjoy their selection of salads (they are famous for their lentils salad) and grilled fish and meat. Open every day for lunch. 
		<p><strong>Nikki Beach:</strong> For a laid back lunch on the beach with the DJ in the background... It's rather "a scene". It can be very noisy. Sun beds can be rented upon availability. Closed on Mondays and Tuesdays.</p> 
		<p><strong>Mango:</strong> Is the bar and restaurant of the “Hotel Christopher”, located right on the water, next to the pool area. On a shaded terrace you can enjoy the scenic view of Lorient and St Jean bays. On the menu: Fresh salads, fish or grilled meat, burgers and Club sandwiches.  Open everyday for lunch.</p>
		<p><strong>Le Restaurant des Pecheurs:</strong> Please see our comment under the dinner section!
		<p><strong>La Gloriette:</strong> Feet in the sand at the edge of the lagoon of Grand-cul-de-sac, La Gloriette invites you to discover its daily changing suggestions of local fish, salads, grills, lobster and homemade dessert. You can relax in the shade of a palm tree, or in a deckchair with a cocktail. Lounge chairs are available on the beach between 12:00 and 3:00 pm. Closed on Wednesdays</p>
		<p><strong>La Langouste:</strong> A good place to eat fresh Caribbean lobster; (6€ per 100gr - great value) with a nice St Barts ambiance and a casual-friendly service. Take the few steps to Flamands beach for a digesting walk or a quick dip in the water. Open for lunch and dinner, closed on Tuesdays.</p>
		<p><strong>Do Brazil:</strong> Up on Shell Beach, beautiful view on the water, fusion food with musical fun ambiance. You can choose between the upstairs restaurant or Do Brazil Snack on the beach. They also offer lounge chairs on the beach. Open every day for lunch.</p>
		<p><strong>Le Grain de Sel:</strong> A casual place next to Saline Beach. It is one of the best places to discover Creole food. They do also offer traditional French dishes, salads and burgers. If you are lucky you will see one of the enormous Iguanas! Closed on Mondays.</p>
		<p><strong>La Plage at Tom Beach Hotel:</strong> is situated next to the airstrip. It is a funky place on the beach to have breakfast, lunch or dinner, otherwise simply enjoy a cocktail and a sunbath. The menu varies from salads, Panini, grilled fish and meat to wok dishes. Open every day.</p>
		<p><strong>Indigo:</strong> Is the beach restaurant of “Small Leading Hotels of the World” GUANAHANI. It overlooks the pool and it offers a large selection of salads, seafood specialities as well as grilled fish and meat. Open every day for lunch and dinner.</p> 
		<p><strong>Le Santa Fe:</strong>  Casual restaurant with a nice view on the Bay of Gouverneur. Enjoy a light lunch before or after your beach time. Open every day except Wednesdays!</p>
  </div>
</div>

